- Data cleaning using drop_na()
- Data transformation using group_by(), summarise(), and pivot_longer()
- Visualization using ggplot2
- Ranking and filtering top-performing games and publishers
- Regional sales comparison and breakdown
- Statistical summaries (mean, median, standard deviation)
- Correlation analysis between regional and global sales
- Linear regression model to predict global sales

### Analyses Included:
- Global sales by genre
- Global sales by platform
- Sales trends over time
- Top 10 games by global sales
- Average sales by genre
- Total sales by region (NA, EU, JP, Other)
- Genre performance across regions
- Top publishers by global sales

### Statistical Modeling:
- Correlation matrix of regional sales vs global sales
- Scatterplot of North America sales vs global sales
- Linear regression model:
  Global_Sales ~ NA_Sales + EU_Sales + JP_Sales + Other_Sales

### Tools Used:
- dplyr for data manipulation
- ggplot2 for visualization
- tidyr for reshaping data
- tibble for improved data structure
